      "id": "theory_oct_to_dec",
      "title": "Converting Octal to Decimal",
      "content": "Converting octal to decimal uses the same place value method as binary and hexadecimal, but with powers of 8!\n\n**Step-by-Step Method:**\n\n1. Write down the octal number\n2. Write the position values (powers of 8) below each digit\n3. Multiply each digit by its position value\n4. Add all the results\n\n**Example 1: Convert 157 (octal) to decimal**\n\nOctal:     1    5    7\nPositions: 64   8    1\nCalculate: 1\u00d764 5\u00d78  7\u00d71\nResults:   64 + 40 + 7 = 111\n\nSo 157 in octal = 111 in decimal!\n\n**Example 2: Convert 725 (octal) to decimal**\n\nOctal:     7    2    5\nPositions: 64   8    1\nCalculate: 7\u00d764 2\u00d78  5\u00d71\nResults:   448 + 16 + 5 = 469\n\nSo 725 in octal = 469 in decimal!\n\n**Example 3: Convert 1000 (octal) to decimal**\n\nOctal:     1    0    0    0\nPositions: 512  64   8    1\nCalculate: 1\u00d7512 0\u00d764 0\u00d78 0\u00d71\nResults:   512 + 0 + 0 + 0 = 512\n\nSo 1000 in octal = 512 in decimal!\n\n**Common Place Values to Remember:**\n\u2022 8\u2070 = 1\n\u2022 8\u00b9 = 8\n\u2022 8\u00b2 = 64\n\u2022 8\u00b3 = 512\n\u2022 8\u2074 = 4096\n\n**Pro Tip:** Just like other conversions, multiply each digit by its power of 8 and add them up. Simple!"
    },
